💜 HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO ME 💜

BEHIND EVERY STRONG WOMAN IS THE ADVERSITY SHE USED TO DRIVE HER FORWARD 🙏🏾⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Happy International Women’s Day to all the women who wakeup EVERY day, put the past behind them, and move full speed ahead toward healing, growth, peace, purpose and their dreams💪🏾⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣⁣My goals for this page have always been for it to be both an outlet to express myself and a tool to inspire others. Typically, I lean a lot on my personal experiences when sharing wisdom but I’m excited to say that I’m currently taking a Mindful, Trauma-Informed Yoga Teacher Training class to learn more formal and research based ways for coaching survivors of trauma through yoga. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m really looking forward to what I learn as I know it will not only benefit the people I influence but myself as well! Thank you to @yoga_medicine for the opportunity 🙏🏾🧘🏾‍♀️⁣⁣

“THE WILDERNESS OF YOUR EXPERIENCES GROWS THE FOREST OF YOUR SOUL.”

Some of the most challenging earthly experiences produce the most positive spiritual outcomes. 🙏🏾

Six years ago I enlisted in the Marine Corps and was shipped to boot camp to be a part of 4th Recruit Training Battalion, November Company, Platoon 4040. Back then women and men trained separately and EVERY female Marine who had ever enlisted was trained in 4th Battalion in #ParrisIsland SC. About two years ago the Marine Corps made the move away from gender separate (but equal) training and integrated the batallions. The decision was made to disband 4th Battalion and today a ceremony was held to celebrate its existence and contributions.

I wasn’t able to make the ceremony but I couldn’t go without commemorating it’s role in my life. I’m honored to have be a part of history and now an even more elite group of women. I will never see burgundy the same way again (#iykyk💯) 💪🏾🙏🏾👑

Forever 4th 🙏🏾

I’ve had the opportunity to do a lot of amazing things and go to a lot of interesting places during my time in the Marine Corps but it all started at 4th Recruit Training Battalion in Parris Island. I’m sad to see the all female battalion disband but I’m grateful for my experience there 🙏🏾 #4RTBN #BleedBurgundy

⁣This isn’t a recruiting post. If you’ve followed me for a while you know female empowerment is something I’m passionate about and 4th Battalion encapsulated that. 

The Marines is unlike other branches in many ways but especially in that there aren’t many women, add on to that black women, in its ranks. 

A lot of us took it for granted but Fourth Battalion was one of the few times in our career where we would be surrounded by so many other women wearing the same uniform. Some of us would graduate from there and go to the fleet where if we were lucky, we’d get to work with one or two other women. 

Fourth Battalion was definitely a valued anomaly that will be missed but it’s impact will never be forgotten ✌🏾
